#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn11.4"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn11.4:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 11 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 11 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn11.4:0.2"
msgid "1. Paṭhamavagga "
msgstr "1. The First Chapter "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn11.4:0.3"
msgid "4. Vepacittisutta "
msgstr "4. With Vepacitti "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.221, pts2ed1.476, sc1
msgctxt "sn11.4:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn11.4:1.2"
msgid "“Bhūtapubbaṃ, bhikkhave, devāsurasaṅgāmo samupabyūḷho ahosi. "
msgstr "“Once upon a time, mendicants, a battle was fought between the gods and the demons. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn11.4:1.3"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vepacitti asurindo asure āmantesi: "
msgstr "Then Vepacitti, lord of demons, addressed the demons, "

#. VAR: parājineyyuṃ → parājeyyuṃ (bj, pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn11.4:1.4"
msgid "‘sace, mārisā, devānaṃ asurasaṅgāme samupabyūḷhe asurā jineyyuṃ devā parājineyyuṃ, yena naṃ sakkaṃ devānamindaṃ kaṇṭhapañcamehi bandhanehi bandhitvā mama santike āneyyātha asurapuran’ti. "
msgstr "‘My good sirs, if the demons defeat the gods in this battle, bind Sakka, the lord of gods, by his limbs and neck and bring him to my presence in the castle of demons.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn11.4:1.5"
msgid "Sakkopi kho, bhikkhave, devānamindo deve tāvatiṃse āmantesi: "
msgstr "Meanwhile, Sakka, lord of gods, addressed the gods of the Thirty-Three, "

msgctxt "sn11.4:1.6"
msgid "‘sace, mārisā, devānaṃ asurasaṅgāme samupabyūḷhe devā jineyyuṃ asurā parājineyyuṃ, yena naṃ vepacittiṃ asurindaṃ kaṇṭhapañcamehi bandhanehi bandhitvā mama santike āneyyātha sudhammasabhan’ti. "
msgstr "‘My good sirs, if the gods defeat the demons in this battle, bind Vepacitti by his limbs and neck and bring him to my presence in the Sudhamma hall of the gods.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: parājiniṃsu → parājiṃsu (bj, pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn11.4:1.7"
msgid "Tasmiṃ kho pana, bhikkhave, saṅgāme devā jiniṃsu, asurā parājiniṃsu. "
msgstr "In that battle the gods won and the demons lost. "

msgctxt "sn11.4:1.8"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, devā tāvatiṃsā vepacittiṃ asurindaṃ kaṇṭhapañcamehi bandhanehi bandhitvā sakkassa devānamindassa santike ānesuṃ sudhammasabhaṃ. "
msgstr "So the gods of the Thirty-Three bound Vepacitti by his limbs and neck and brought him to Sakka’s presence in the Sudhamma hall of the gods. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn11.4:1.9"
msgid "Tatra sudaṃ, bhikkhave, vepacitti asurindo kaṇṭhapañcamehi bandhanehi baddho sakkaṃ devānamindaṃ sudhammasabhaṃ pavisantañca nikkhamantañca asabbhāhi pharusāhi vācāhi akkosati paribhāsati. "
msgstr "And as Sakka was entering and leaving the hall, Vepacitti abused and insulted him with rude, harsh words. "

msgctxt "sn11.4:1.10"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, mātali saṅgāhako sakkaṃ devānamindaṃ gāthāhi ajjhabhāsi: "
msgstr "So Mātali the charioteer addressed Sakka in verse, "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn11.4:2.1"
msgid "‘Bhayā nu maghavā sakka, "
msgstr "‘O Maghavā, O Sakka, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.4:2.2"
msgid "dubbalyā no titikkhasi; "
msgstr "is it from fear or from weakness "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.4:2.3"
msgid "Suṇanto pharusaṃ vācaṃ, "
msgstr "that you put up with such harsh words "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.4:2.4"
msgid "sammukhā vepacittino’ti. "
msgstr "in the presence of Vepacitti?’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn11.4:3.1"
msgid "‘Nāhaṃ bhayā na dubbalyā, "
msgstr "‘It’s not out of fear or weakness "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.4:3.2"
msgid "khamāmi vepacittino; "
msgstr "that I’m patient with Vepacitti. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.4:3.3"
msgid "Kathañhi mādiso viññū, "
msgstr "For how can a sensible person like me "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.4:3.4"
msgid "bālena paṭisaṃyuje’ti. "
msgstr "get in a fight with a fool?’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn11.4:4.1"
msgid "‘Bhiyyo bālā pabhijjeyyuṃ, "
msgstr "‘Fools would vent even more "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.4:4.2"
msgid "no cassa paṭisedhako; "
msgstr "if there’s no-one to put a stop to them. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.4:4.3"
msgid "Tasmā bhusena daṇḍena, "
msgstr "So a wise one should stop "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.4:4.4"
msgid "dhīro bālaṃ nisedhaye’ti. "
msgstr "a fool with forceful punishment.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn11.4:5.1"
msgid "‘Etadeva ahaṃ maññe, "
msgstr "‘I think that this is the only way "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.4:5.2"
msgid "bālassa paṭisedhanaṃ; "
msgstr "to put a stop to a fool, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.4:5.3"
msgid "Paraṃ saṅkupitaṃ ñatvā, "
msgstr "when you know that the other is upset, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.4:5.4"
msgid "yo sato upasammatī’ti. "
msgstr "be mindful and stay calm.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.478, sc6
msgctxt "sn11.4:6.1"
msgid "‘Etadeva titikkhāya, "
msgstr "‘I see this fault, Vāsava, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.4:6.2"
msgid "vajjaṃ passāmi vāsava; "
msgstr "in just being patient. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.4:6.3"
msgid "Yadā naṃ maññati bālo, "
msgstr "When a fool thinks, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.4:6.4"
msgid "bhayā myāyaṃ titikkhati; "
msgstr "“He puts up with me out of fear,” "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.4:6.5"
msgid "Ajjhāruhati dummedho, "
msgstr "the idiot will go after you even harder, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.4:6.6"
msgid "gova bhiyyo palāyinan’ti. "
msgstr "like a cow chasing someone who runs away.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.222, sc7
msgctxt "sn11.4:7.1"
msgid "‘Kāmaṃ maññatu vā mā vā, "
msgstr "‘Let him think this if he wishes, or not—"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.4:7.2"
msgid "bhayā myāyaṃ titikkhati; "
msgstr "“He puts up with me out of fear.” "

# NOTE: I follow BB’s interpretation here. I’m not very happy with it, but can’t fault it.
#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.4:7.3"
msgid "Sadatthaparamā atthā, "
msgstr "Of goals culminating in one’s own good, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.4:7.4"
msgid "khantyā bhiyyo na vijjati. "
msgstr "none better than patience is found. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "sn11.4:8.1"
msgid "Yo have balavā santo, "
msgstr "When a strong person "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.4:8.2"
msgid "dubbalassa titikkhati; "
msgstr "puts up with a weakling, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.4:8.3"
msgid "Tamāhu paramaṃ khantiṃ, "
msgstr "they call that the ultimate patience, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.4:8.4"
msgid "niccaṃ khamati dubbalo. "
msgstr "for a weakling must always be patient. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "sn11.4:9.1"
msgid "Abalaṃ taṃ balaṃ āhu, "
msgstr "The strength of folly "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.4:9.2"
msgid "yassa bālabalaṃ balaṃ; "
msgstr "is really just weakness, they say. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.4:9.3"
msgid "Balassa dhammaguttassa, "
msgstr "But no-one can challenge a person "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.4:9.4"
msgid "paṭivattā na vijjati. "
msgstr "who’s strong, guarded by the teaching. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.479, sc10
msgctxt "sn11.4:10.1"
msgid "Tasseva tena pāpiyo, "
msgstr "When you get angry at an angry person "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.4:10.2"
msgid "yo kuddhaṃ paṭikujjhati; "
msgstr "you just make things worse for yourself. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.4:10.3"
msgid "Kuddhaṃ appaṭikujjhanto, "
msgstr "When you don’t get angry at an angry person "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.4:10.4"
msgid "saṅgāmaṃ jeti dujjayaṃ. "
msgstr "you win a battle hard to win. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc11
msgctxt "sn11.4:11.1"
msgid "Ubhinnamatthaṃ carati, "
msgstr "When you know that the other is angry, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.4:11.2"
msgid "attano ca parassa ca; "
msgstr "you act for the good of both "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.4:11.3"
msgid "Paraṃ saṅkupitaṃ ñatvā, "
msgstr "yourself and the other "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.4:11.4"
msgid "yo sato upasammati. "
msgstr "if you’re mindful and stay calm. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12
msgctxt "sn11.4:12.1"
msgid "Ubhinnaṃ tikicchantānaṃ, "
msgstr "People unfamiliar with the teaching "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.4:12.2"
msgid "attano ca parassa ca; "
msgstr "consider one who heals both "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.4:12.3"
msgid "Janā maññanti bāloti, "
msgstr "oneself and the other "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn11.4:12.4"
msgid "ye dhammassa akovidā’ti. "
msgstr "to be a fool.’ "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: sc13
msgctxt "sn11.4:13.1"
msgid "So hi nāma, bhikkhave, sakko devānamindo sakaṃ puññaphalaṃ upajīvamāno devānaṃ tāvatiṃsānaṃ issariyādhipaccaṃ rajjaṃ kārento khantisoraccassa vaṇṇavādī bhavissati. "
msgstr "So, mendicants, even Sakka, lord of gods—while living off of the fruit of his good and bad deeds, and ruling as sovereign lord over these gods of the Thirty-Three—will speak in praise of patience and gentleness. "

msgctxt "sn11.4:13.2"
msgid "Idha kho taṃ, bhikkhave, sobhetha yaṃ tumhe evaṃ svākkhāte dhammavinaye pabbajitā samānā khamā ca bhaveyyātha soratā cā”ti. "
msgstr "But since you have gone forth in such a well explained teaching and training, it would be truly beautiful for you to be patient and gentle!”"

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
